  26:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****                         ##### How to use this driver #####
  27:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****   ==============================================================================
  28:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      [..]
  29:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      The LTDC HAL driver can be used as follows:
  30:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  31:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      (#) Declare a LTDC_HandleTypeDef handle structure, for example: LTDC_HandleTypeDef  hltdc;
  32:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  33:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      (#) Initialize the LTDC low level resources by implementing the HAL_LTDC_MspInit() API:
  34:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          (##) Enable the LTDC interface clock
  35:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          (##) NVIC configuration if you need to use interrupt process
  36:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****              (+++) Configure the LTDC interrupt priority
  37:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****              (+++) Enable the NVIC LTDC IRQ Channel
  38:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  39:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      (#) Initialize the required configuration through the following parameters:
  40:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          the LTDC timing, the horizontal and vertical polarity, the pixel clock polarity,
  41:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          Data Enable polarity and the LTDC background color value using HAL_LTDC_Init() function
  42:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  43:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      *** Configuration ***
  44:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      =========================
  45:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      [..]
  46:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      (#) Program the required configuration through the following parameters:
  47:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          the pixel format, the blending factors, input alpha value, the window size
  48:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          and the image size using HAL_LTDC_ConfigLayer() function for foreground
  49:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          or/and background layer.
  50:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  51:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      (#) Optionally, configure and enable the CLUT using HAL_LTDC_ConfigCLUT() and
  52:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          HAL_LTDC_EnableCLUT functions.
  53:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  54:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      (#) Optionally, enable the Dither using HAL_LTDC_EnableDither().
  55:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  56:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      (#) Optionally, configure and enable the Color keying using HAL_LTDC_ConfigColorKeying()
  57:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          and HAL_LTDC_EnableColorKeying functions.
  58:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  59:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      (#) Optionally, configure LineInterrupt using HAL_LTDC_ProgramLineEvent()
  60:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          function
  61:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  62:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      (#) If needed, reconfigure and change the pixel format value, the alpha value
  63:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          value, the window size, the window position and the layer start address
  64:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          for foreground or/and background layer using respectively the following
  65:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          functions: HAL_LTDC_SetPixelFormat(), HAL_LTDC_SetAlpha(), HAL_LTDC_SetWindowSize(),
  66:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          HAL_LTDC_SetWindowPosition() and HAL_LTDC_SetAddress().
  67:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  68:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      (#) Variant functions with _NoReload suffix allows to set the LTDC configuration/settings with
  69:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          This is useful in case when the program requires to modify serval LTDC settings (on one or
  70:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          then applying(reload) these settings in one shot by calling the function HAL_LTDC_Reload()
  71:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  72:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          After calling the _NoReload functions to set different color/format/layer settings,
  73:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          the program shall call the function HAL_LTDC_Reload() to apply(reload) these settings.
  74:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          Function HAL_LTDC_Reload() can be called with the parameter ReloadType set to LTDC_RELOAD_
  75:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          an immediate reload is required.
  76:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          Function HAL_LTDC_Reload() can be called with the parameter ReloadType set to LTDC_RELOAD_
  77:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          the reload should be done in the next vertical blanking period,
  78:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****          this option allows to avoid display flicker by applying the new settings during the vertic
  79:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  80:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
  81:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c ****      (#) To control LTDC state you can use the following function: HAL_LTDC_GetState()
  82:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ltdc.c **** 
